        content:
          "<p>(Reuters) - Boeing Co &lt;BA.N&gt; said on Friday it would resume operations at production facilities in Philadelphia next week after a two week suspension due to the spread of the coronavirus.</p>\n<p>The company said operations at its Philadelphia plants, which manufacture military rotorcraft including the H-47 Chinook, V-22 Osprey and MH-139A Grey Wolf, would restart on Monday with enhanced safety measures.</p>\n<p>Boeing said on Thursday it would resume the production of commercial jets next week in Washington state.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>(Reporting by Uday Sampath in Bengaluru; Editing by Anil D'Silva)</p>",
